# UI Design Tokens

## Context

- Apply when defining CSS variables, Tailwind theme configuration, or styling components.
- All colors, spacing, and shape values must come from these tokens.
- Never freehand random colors or spacing values.

## Requirements

### Core Color Palette

- Define these as CSS variables in `:root` or Tailwind theme tokens.
- `ink` (outline/shadow): `#1A1A21` (near-black)
- `paper` (surface): `#F5F7F7`
- `purpleA` (primary bg): `#413DE1`
- `purpleB` (secondary bg): `#8164ED`
- `cyanA`: `#4CEAFD`
- `cyanB`: `#3BC4FB`
- `green`: `#29F724`
- `red`: `#FE3F3B`
- `yellow`: `#DEFD4E`

### Gradients

- Background gradient: `linear-gradient(180deg, #413DE1 0%, #8164ED 100%)`
- Accent gradient: `linear-gradient(135deg, #4CEAFD 0%, #3BC4FB 100%)`
- Warm gradient (alt screens): `linear-gradient(180deg, #FE686F 0%, #F3A43E 100%)`

### Shape and Depth Tokens

- `radiusCard`: `24px`
- `radiusButton`: `18px` (or `999px` for full pills)
- `borderW`: `4px` (default), `3px` for smaller elements
- `shadowOffset`: `8px` (cards), `6px` (buttons)
- `shadow`: `8px 8px 0 #1A1A21` (cards), `6px 6px 0 #1A1A21` (buttons)

### Spacing Tokens (Mobile)

- `gutter`: `16px`
- `stackGap`: `12px`
- `hudHeight`: `44pxâ€“56px`
- `tapHeight`: `56px` minimum for answer options

### Tailwind Utility Classes

- Create custom utilities in `globals.css`:
  - `.shadow-sticker`: `box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink)`
  - `.shadow-sticker-sm`: `box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink)`
  - `.border-ink`: `border-color: var(--ink)`
  - `.bg-paper`: `background: var(--paper)`
  - `.bg-arcade`: base gradient background class

## Examples

<example>
  Valid CSS variable definition:
  
  ```css
  :root {
    --ink: #1A1A21;
    --paper: #F5F7F7;
    --purpleA: #413DE1;
    --purpleB: #8164ED;
    --green: #29F724;
    --red: #FE3F3B;
  }
  ```
</example>

<example type="invalid">
  Invalid: Using hardcoded colors in components instead of tokens:
  
  ```css
  .button {
    border: 4px solid #000000; /* Should use --ink */
    background: #FFFFFF; /* Should use --paper */
  }
  ```
</example>

<example>
  Valid Tailwind component class:
  
  ```html
  <div class="bg-paper border-4 border-ink rounded-[24px] shadow-sticker">
  ```
</example>

<example type="invalid">
  Invalid: Mixing custom utilities with random inline styles:
  
  ```html
  <div class="bg-paper shadow-sticker" style="border: 2px solid gray; border-radius: 12px;">
  ```
</example>
